extras.promotionMessage: Designed by our medical team to provide a good overview of your current health status. It includes 8 health areas with 50 biomarkers and a personal medical comment.

bodies.Overview: Designed by our medical team to provide a good overview of your current health status. It includes 8 health areas with 50 biomarkers and a personal medical report.
bodies.Cardiovascular: Cardiovascular disease is the leading cause of death in the world, but it can be prevented. Dyslipidemia (excess of triglycerides and cholesterol in blood) is one of the most important risk factors. High levels can effectively be controlled through diet and exercise.
bodies.Inflammation: Increased markers of inflammation can be due to a number of causes including infection, joint problems and can even be a risk factor for heart disease.
bodies.Diabetes: Diabetes occurs when the body’s ability to regulate the amount of blood sugar (glucose) is impaired. In type 1 diabetes the body is no longer able to produce insulin, and in the more common type 2 (which occurs more frequently with age) the body is no longer sensitive to its action. Lifestyle changes can prevent pre-diabetes from progressing to type 2 diabetes, as well as being effective in treatment. The purpose of diabetes related tests is to detect pre-diabetes and undiagnosed diabetes, as well as to monitor how well the diabetes is controlled.
bodies.Blood status: There are 3 main types of cells in the blood – platelets (important for stopping bleeding), white cells (to fight infection) and red cells (carries oxygen around the body). A full blood count provides information about these cells. For example, if someone is feeling tired frequently, the blood status can determine whether anaemia (low red cells) is a cause for this.
bodies.Kidney function: The kidney profile consists of a set of tests used to evaluate the function of the kidneys. Kidneys remove waste products and excess water from the body. If not functioning properly, waste products can accumulate and make an individual unwell. There are a number of reasons that the kidneys may not be working correctly including diabetes and cardiovascular disease.
bodies.Liver function: The liver is essential for digesting food as well as removing the body of toxic substances. If the liver is not functioning correctly it can make an individual unwell. There are a number of causes for a liver not functioning correctly including infection, alcohol use, and certain medications and food supplements.
bodies.Vitamins and Minerals: Vitamins and minerals are essential nutrients that are required by the body to work properly and stay healthy. There are 13 main types of vitamins – such as Vitamin D, and a number of minerals such as iron. Ensuring an adequate amount of vitamins and minerals is crucial for the regulation of many bodily functions, such as the formation of blood cells, tissues, genetic material and hormones.
bodies.Other: For men taking this test, PSA (Prostate Specific Antigen) levels are also included. PSA is a protein which produced by the prostate, with high levels often associated with prostate cancer.

docs.name: Dev Estudio de fertilidad Melio

bodies.Hormonas sexuales: Es requisito imprescindible para la concepción que la función ovárica esté conservada. Estudio de hormonas asociadas a reserva ovárica o a fertilidad.
bodies.Hemograma: Un hemograma es el análisis de un grupo de biomarcadores que da información acerca de los 3 tipos de células en la sangre. Se utiliza de manera habitual para detectar casos de anemia, infección y el estudio de enfermedades hematológicas. Es especialmente importante en el diagnóstico de anemias combinado con un perfil férrico.
bodies.Perfil tiroideo: El tiroides es una glándula situada en el cuello que produce las hormonas encargadas del control del metabolismo o la regulación del uso y almacenamiento de energía corporal. El perfil tiroideo se utiliza para evaluar la función tiroidea como diagnóstico y control del hipotiroidismo y del hipertiroidismo.
bodies.Prolactina: La prolactina (PRL) es una hormona secretada por la parte anterior de la hipófisis, que estimula la producción de leche en las glándulas mamarias y la síntesis de progesterona por el cuerpo lúteo en el ovario.

docs.description: Con un simple análisis de sangre Melio te ayudamos a tener información sobre las hormonas clave asociadas a la fertilidad femenina. Con Melio tendrás el mismo análisis que en una clínica a una fracción del precio habitual incluyendo una estimación de tu reserva ovárica. Sin cita previa, sin esperas, simplemente acude a un centro y obtén tus resultados. Esta prueba debe realizarse entre el tercer y el quinto día del ciclo menstrual.
docs.h3: Sin cita previa. Resultados rápidos y fiables
docs.m1: Resultados revisados por un especialista con un comentario personalizado. No esperes, sin cita previa, resultados en 48 horas.
docs.m2: Recuerda hacer la prueba entre el tercer y el quinto día del ciclo. Incluye hormona antimulleriana.

docs.h1: Nasopharyngeal swab test carried out by a trained health professional
docs.h2: Includes a medical review and Fit-To-Fly certificate
docs.h3: RT-PCR test for direct detection of the SARS-CoV-2 virus
docs.m2: Including a personalised medical report by a GMC registered doctor and Fit-To-Fly certificate for negative cases.
docs.description:
This swab test is taken at one of our London locations, by a trained professional. The price includes a medical review and a Fit-To-Fly certificate for negative PCR results.

The test is used to tell whether or not you currently have the virus. It involves taking a swab from the inside of your nose and the back of your throat. 

A negative PCR test may be required for travelling to certain destinations. For tests taken Monday - Thursday, you can expect to get your results within 48 hours. For tests taken on a Friday, results will be delivered on Monday evening.

docs.name: NIPT
docs.description:
Non-Invasive Prenatal Testing (NIPT) is a screening test that looks at the baby’s DNA in the mother’s bloodstream to identify if the baby is affected by certain chromosomal abnormalities.

The NIPT test is a targeted tested which will identify if the baby has a chance of being affected by Trisomy 21 (Down’s Syndrome), Trisomy 18 (Edwards’ Syndrome) and Trisomy 13 (Patau’s Syndrome).

docs.name: COVID-19 Detailed Antibody Test
docs.h1: Blood test carried out by a trained health professional
docs.h2: Helps you determine if the infection was recent.
docs.h3: Identifies the presence of both IgM and IgG antibodies separately
docs.m1: IgM and IgG antibody results delivered together with a medical report to your personal digital journal.
docs.description:
This is a test for those who want to know if they have had a COVID-19 infection, with or without symptoms. IgM and IgG results are analysed separately, which can help you determine if the infection was recent or happened a long time ago. Antibody tests should be done at least 3 weeks after onset of disease for accurate results.

The blood draw will be done at one of our locations . Th test analysis is done by an accredited laboratory, and it detects the presence ofIgM and IgG antibodies. Your test result will tell you if you have SARS-CoV-2 antibodies in your blood, and which class they belong to (IgM and/or IgG).

Please note that it is not yet known if, or to which degree, COVID-19 antibodies can offer protection against future infection, or for how long any potential immunity will last. You should also know that some people may have recovered from a COVID-19 infection without having detectable levels of antibodies in their blood.
